  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nAlloy\n10\n2\n0\nElemental\n(non-survivor food)\n20\nDropped by\n(16.67%)\n\"alloy\"\n“Ahoy there, alloy!”\n–Wilson\n“Fire makes everything better.”\n–Willow\n“Fire make it strong like Wolfgang.”\n–Wolfgang\n“Cold and hard, like my existence.”\n–Wendy\n“PRECIOUS METAL”\n–WX-78\n“Iron that has gone through metallic bonding.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“It's like a wood block made out of metal.”\n–Woodie\n“Durable.”\n–Maxwell\n“Ah, refined metal. As good as any factory could produce.”\n–Wagstaff\n“A metal wörthy öf the Söns öf Ivaldi.”\n–Wigfrid\n“Gosh. That's a lot of metal.”\n–Webber\n“Hope this is worth all the trouble.”\n–Walani\n“Metal cooked well done.”\n–Warly\n“Ahoy, alloy!”\n–Woodlegs\n“IS'T BLOCK O' HARD METALS”\n–Wilba\n“Bar of Clink Rock”\n–Wormwood\n“Heavy metal made heavier.”\n–Wheeler\nAlloy is a resource exclusive to the Hamlet DLC. It is obtained by refining Iron Ore in a Smelter and is required for several Crafting recipes. There is a 16.67% chance to spawn a single Alloy in the Secret Bandit Camp.\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\n×4\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×6\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×3\n×3\n×3\nView or edit this template\nResources\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/behavior/function/tags of these items\nPlants\nNatural non-living materials\nMobs Parts\nSkins\nFeathers\nBones and horns\nGems\nShadow Resources\nLunar Resources\nCraftable Resources\nNon-natural materials\nTrinkets\nLost Relics\nTransmission Items",
